      "span_text": "However, in dilated cardiomyopathy, stepwise afterload reduction and the concomitant increase in shortening amplitudes were associated with extraordinary alterations in the shape of the calcium transients: the amplitude rose, the time to peak was delayed, and at minimal afterloads, a long-lasting plateau was observed, he intracellular calcium transient of normal human myocardium is modulated during the performance of mechanical work.1)2 The ability to perform mechanical work (to shorten against a given afterload) was depressed in skinned myocardial fibers of patients with dilated cardiomyopathy, although the crossbridge cycling rate was normal. The intracellular calcium transient of intact working human myocardium of patients with dilated cardiomyopathy had not yet been analyzed."
